sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant T as Telegram API
    participant n8n

    U->>T: send command (/status or other)

    Note over n8n: Node 1 - Schedule Trigger (every minute)
    n8n->>T: getUpdates (Node 2 - HTTP Request)
    T-->>n8n: list of recent messages

    n8n->>n8n: Node 3 - Code: filter recent messages

    alt /status
        n8n->>n8n: Node 4 - Switch → /status branch
        n8n->>n8n: Node B - Read File from Disk
        n8n->>n8n: Node C - Code: count files
        n8n->>T: Node D - Telegram: send message (fixed Chat ID)
        T-->>U: file summary
    else fallback
        n8n->>n8n: Node 4 - Switch → Fallback Output
        n8n->>n8n: Node 5 - IF: text matches regex
        n8n->>T: Node 6 - Telegram: send reply (fixed Chat ID)
        T-->>U: automatic reply
    end
